# CODEOWNERS — only CATASTROPHIC / IRREVERSIBLE paths need an owner.
# Everything else moves freely (no bottleneck). A mistake on the paths below can't be cleanly undone,
# so they require a code-owner's review before merging into main (turn on "Require review from
# Code Owners" in branch protection to enforce this).
#
# Replace the placeholders with real GitHub usernames, e.g. @your-github-username.
#   [REPO_OWNER]        = the founder / repo owner
#   [PRIMARY_REVIEWER]  = whoever approves governance changes (often the same person)
#   [TECHNICAL_REVIEWER]= optional second owner for code/migrations

# Irreversible — a mistake here can't be cleanly undone
**/migrations/**            [REPO_OWNER] [TECHNICAL_REVIEWER]
**/*.sql                    [REPO_OWNER] [TECHNICAL_REVIEWER]
.env*                       [REPO_OWNER]
.gitignore                  [REPO_OWNER]

# The review/merge gate itself — weakening this dilutes every other guarantee
/.github/                   [REPO_OWNER] [PRIMARY_REVIEWER]

# The brain's constitution + the skill/hook engine (governs every session + agent)
/CLAUDE.md                  [REPO_OWNER] [PRIMARY_REVIEWER]
/.claude/skills/            [REPO_OWNER] [PRIMARY_REVIEWER]
/.claude/settings.json      [REPO_OWNER] [PRIMARY_REVIEWER]
/.claude/hooks/             [REPO_OWNER] [PRIMARY_REVIEWER]

# Deliberately NOT owner-gated: your normal docs, deliverables, and day-to-day work move freely.
